Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} into sticks (like fries; ours were 3 inches long and 1⁄3-inch thick). Finely chop a few @Sliced Dill Pickle{1%slice} until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4 servings). (Save remaining pickle slices for serving.) Drain and rinse @Kidney Beans{1%unit}. Trim and mince @Scallions{2%unit}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon}. Season with @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}.

Roast on top rack until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Secret Sauce ==

While carrots roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, chopped @Dill Pickle{4%tsp}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and as much @Hot Sauce{to taste} as you like.

== Bean Patties ==

Meanwhile, place half the @Kidney Beans{1%unit} (all for 4 servings) in a #large bowl{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until mostly smooth. (It's OK if there are still some larger pieces.)

Stir in @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}, scallions, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @Cajun Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, 3/4 of the @Tempura Batter{82%g}, and 3 TBSP @Water{3%tablespoon} until thoroughly combined. (For 4, use all the tempura batter mix and 1/4 cup water.) Season with @Salt{1/4%tsp} (we used 1/4 tsp; 1/2 tsp for 4) and @Pepper{pinch}.

Divide bean mixture into two mounds (four mounds for 4).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Using a #rubber spatula{}, add bean mixture mounds to pan and gently press to flatten into patties, each about as wide as a burger bun.

Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Transfer patties to a #plate{}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches, adding another drizzle of
> oil before each batch.

== Assembly ==

Halve and toast @Brioche Buns{2%unit} until golden; spread cut sides with 2 TBSP @Butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Spread bottom buns with up to half the secret sauce. Fill buns with patties and as much sliced pickle as you like.

Divide sandwiches between plates. Serve with carrot fries and remaining secret sauce on the side.